results.name: Number of labeled graphs having n blue nodes and n green ones, where edges join only nodes of different colors.
reference: H. S. Wilf, Generatingfunctionology, 2nd edn., Academic Press, NY, 1994, p. 88.
example: a(1) = 4 because we have B G, B--G, G B and G--B, where B (G) stands for a blue (green) node and -- denotes an edge.
results.author: _Emeric Deutsch_, Aug 09 2005
